visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple already considers the first HomePod \u2018vintage\u2019", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-01T17:38:56+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Apple Watch, Garmin Epix, Fitbit, and Amazfit Bip fitness trackers on a stylized blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9NfU5CzAkm1H45234kKpT8gicKk=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70657030/acastro_220321_5092_0001.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>From simple fitness bands and rugged sports watches to rings, these are the best trackers you can get.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22985108/best-fitness-tracker\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "id": 800297, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22985108/best-fitness-tracker", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The best fitness trackers to buy right now", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-01T17:14:15+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot of Instagram\u2019s mobile app displaying a picture with the \u201cAI Info\u201d tag applied to it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/9duhrbAiygTaYZOKtNuCKTvCh1s=/0x133:1723x1282/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73438208/01_IG_AI_Generated_Content_Lable_Carousel_01_2_crop.0.jpg\" />\