388/supreme-court-ruling-moody-paxton-texas-florida-social-media-law", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Supreme Court rules in major internet speech cases", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-01T14:30:05+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Fg5oUdHwUGthoRbNgSNgWfnvQqs=/0x180:1080x900/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73437781/R2_Image_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Samsung is bringing Matter 1.2 to its SmartThings smart home platform.</em> | Image: Samsung SmartThings</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ld3N1h\">Samsung SmartThings looks set to become the first major smart home platform to fully support <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/23/23925489/matter-1-2-smart-home-support-new-devices\">Matter 1.2</a>. According to a <a href=\"https://news.samsung.com/us/samsung-smartthings-simplifies-smart-home-experience-with-latest-app-updates/\">press release</a>, the SmartThings platform now works with Matter 1.2, so manufacturers and developers can start integrating their compatible devices with the platform. The SmartThings app won\u2019t be updated to support Matter until later this summer \u2014 so you won\u2019t be able to control your Matter-comp", "id": 799432, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/1/24189785/samsung-smartthings-matter-1-2-support-robot-vacuums", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail":